findings.title: Out of gas
findings.description: The functions includeInReward() and _getCurrentSupply() use loops that can cause an OUT_OF_GAS exception if the excluded addresses list is too long.

findings.title: Owner privileges (In the period when the owner is not renounced)
findings.description: The contract owner has excessive privileges to modify critical parameters and functions, including tax, dev and liquidity fee, maximum transaction amount, exclusion from fees, dev address, router address, minimum number of tokens for liquidity, and lock/unlock functionality. This could lead to potential security risks even after ownership is renounced.
